Preheat oven to 350 deg. F (180 deg. C). Cream together shortening and granulated sugar. Beat in 4 eggs, then stir in flour, salt and baking soda. Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls on to ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 350 deg. F (180 deg. C) for 10 to 12 minutes. Prepare frosting by combining melted butter, vanilla, 1 egg, and powdered sugar in a medium bowl. Beat with electric mixer until smooth. Frost cookies when they are cool.